remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` provides static methods for encoding images and image sequences to
WebP format. Single-frame encoding is handled by the `Encode` overloads, while
multi-frame (animated) encoding is handled by `EncodeAnimated`.

The encoder does not hold any state or resources and does not need to be disposed.

## Examples

```csharp
// Encode a single frame to a byte array
using var bitmap = new SKBitmap(200, 200);
using var canvas = new SKCanvas(bitmap);
canvas.Clear(SKColors.SkyBlue);

using var pixmap = bitmap.PeekPixels();
var options = new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossless, 100);
using SKData data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(pixmap, options);
File.WriteAllBytes("output.webp", data.ToArray());
```
